span.font: Local server generates a unique encryption salt
Password is hashed and stored in the DB along with the salt
Server returns JWT token and salt to the client
Server verifies credentials and returns JWT token and stored salt
Client stores the token and salt
If needed, user enters master password in MasterPasswordModal
AuthContext uses PBKDF2 (master password + salt) to derive the encryption key
The derived encryption key can be used to encrypt and decrypt sensitive data locally
